The article discusses the author's investment agenda in America, which aims to mobilize private sector manufacturing and clean energy investments, creating jobs in the process. Specifically, the author highlights the progress made in the solar industry, with 51 new and expanded solar equipment manufacturing plants announced and an eight-fold increase in domestic solar panel manufacturing capacity. The author emphasizes that their plan is effective and mentions vetoing H.J. Res. 39 to avoid creating uncertainty for American businesses and workers in the solar industry. The focus is on maintaining energy security and expanding U.S. capacity in preparation for the conclusion of a temporary bridge in June 2024.